Here's what was done: Front cocking serrations taken off, Slide stop nub cut flush and frame countersunk, Spare Ed Brown extractor fit and re-finished as well (which will be included), 10-8 rear sight installed and a Novak front tritium sight with a white ring. Finish is matte Ionbond DLC. The gun is tight, but was never impossible to rack when I received it as you often hear regarding Baers. It's got a very tight slide to frame fit and a very tight bushing that requires a wrench to turn. The gun is very accurate, more accurate than me. The only flaw is there is a very slight scratch on the frame that I have tried to capture in a photo. It's hard to photograph as it is very slight. The round count is unknown, but I have put less than 500 rounds through it, and less than 300 since the refinish work 1.5 years ago. Included will be 2 Baer mags and a Chip Mccormick mag, the spare extractor, the original box and certificate. Asking $1,600, would prefer to meet at a local shop for a transfer.  I will ship, but those costs will be extra.
